  "assessment": "Equation balancing converts the isolated 0.35% result into a genuine adaptive free-boundary branch through achieved beta 0.790%. The limiting physical components shift between FSQR and FSQL, requiring static then norm-derived lambda scaling. Cadence 20 remains the best globalization screen. At target beta 0.7040625%, increasing total Krylov work at restart 80 does not converge, while expanding the Arnoldi basis to 120 converges in 121 corrector iterations. At target 0.72%, width 120 remains GPU-bound after 578 seconds, while width 160 converges in 171 iterations and releases through NESTOR in 3. Width 160 then accepts targets 0.735%, 0.75%, and 0.775% in 291, 411, and 431 corrector iterations. The endpoint remains close to the 1e-8 component gate; continuation toward 1% must retain small pressure steps and the wider basis before deciding whether a coupled block preconditioner is necessary."
